  "text": "In order to validate the result, the method proposed in [CITATION_1] has been used to design all the ARRs. It has led to the fault signature given by Table 2 . According to these results, the constraint sets that cannot be discriminated are {k 2 , k 6 } and {k 7 , k 8 }. The constraint set that cannot be detected is {k 1 , k 4 , k 10 } and the diagnosable constraints are {k 3 , k 5 , k 9 , k 11 , k 12 }. Applying the function Φ : K Σ −→ C Σ , it is obvious that the components that cannot be discriminated are {c 2 , c 6 } and {c 7 , c 8 }, the components that cannot be detected are {c 1 , c 4 , c 10 }, and the diagnosable components are {c 3 , c 5 , c 9 , c 11 , c 12 }.",
